{"履修期": "春学期後半", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "This course explores challenges faced by companies that conduct overseas business across a multitude of different cultures, languages, and traditions, not to mention economic, political, and technological landscapes. This course explains how managers can adapt leadership, strategies, and operations to thrive in the evolving global environments with concepts and practical cases. The course will cover the basics of international management, including global strategic positioning, entry strategies and alliances, effective cross-cultural understanding and management, and the development and retention of an effective global management team. Through these topics, students will develop the ability to understand, apply, and interpret the international business environment to design competitive management strategies.", "到達目標": "Upon successful completion of the course, students will be able to assess the international business environment (political, economic, legal, and technological), manage interdependence (social responsibility, ethics, sustainability), understand the role of culture in cross-cultural negotiation and decision-making, formulate and implement strategies for strategic alliances, small businesses, and emerging-economy firms, and motivating employees (staffing, training, and compensation for global operations). &nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "<span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Basic Management 1, Economics</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>", "授業の概要・背景": "", "授業方法": "This is a face-to-face class.&nbsp;   The